@node CustomControls.RandomSequential "IceIQle, CustomControls: RandomSequential"
SEQUENTIAL AND RANDOM PHRASE SELECTION (%R & %S controls)
---------------------------------------------------------

    For the %R and %S controls, the OPTIONAL '@' character can be any
    character you choose and is used to delimit phrases in the text file.
    This is to allow the possibility of multiple line phrases. The
    extracted text will start with the character after the '@' character
    in your text file, and end at the next '@' character. The delimiter
    characters must appear in the first column of each line they occur
    in to be recognized. This allows use of the character in your text.
    If you don't specify any delimiter, (eg. %R"FileName"), then the file
    is assumed to contain single line phrases.
    It is perfectly legitimate to include any % codes within your text
    files. This includes %R, %S, %V, %I and %C, but recursion is limited
    to 10 levels to prevent an endless loop, if for example, you try to
    include the same file repeatedly.

    To use %R or %S, the first line of your phrase files MUST contain
    the total number of phrases in the file, and the second line MUST
    contain the current phrase number to be used for the next sequential
    inclusion. The first number is read by IceIQle and is used for
    determining the highest random phrase to select from. The second
    number is read and incremented by one each time the %S control is
    used. When the next phrase number exceeds the maximum phrase number,
    it is set back to 000001. Both numbers must exist in the file,
    regardless of whether or not you use both %R and %S.

      NOTE: IT IS ASSUMED THAT THE SECOND NUMBER (Next Phrase #)
            CONSISTS OF 6 DIGITS. THEREFORE, IF YOU WANT TO START
            THE SEQUENCE AT THE FIRST PHRASE, USE 000001 AS THE NUMBER.
            If you use fewer digits, IceIQle will overwrite 4 or 5
            characters of your first phrase the first time %S is used.

            ALSO, IT IS ASSUMED that both numbers start in the first
            column of the Line.

    Using an @{" index file " link Doc.CountingIndex} associated with phrase files will significantly
    speed up inclusion of phrases. If an index exists, it will
    automatically be used. If the date stamp of the index is older than
    that of the phrase file, a requester allowing regeneration of the
    index will be presented.

         EXAMPLE 2)

         If you have a collection of one line headers defined in a file
         called "Headers", and you want them used sequentially,
         you could simply use:

                 HEADER=%S"Headers"

         See the @{" TAGLINE " link ToolTypes.TagLine} tooltype for a more complex example.

@endnode

@node CustomControls.SigDependant "IceIQle, CustomControls: SigDependant"
VARIABLE SIG DEPENDENT STRINGS (The %V"FileName" control) [IceBBS Only]
---------------------------------------------------------

    The text file indicated by the FileName contains pairs of SIG names
    and strings. The strings can contain constant text as well as any
    valid control codes including %R, %S, %V, %I, and %C. One space must
    seperate the SIG name from the text string. The special name
    'DefaultSig' indicates the text to generate for any SIG not included
    in the file. If you don't include a DefaultSig line, nothing will be
    outputted if the SIG isn't found elsewhere in the file. From EMail,
    the DefaultSig string will always be used.

        EXAMPLE 3)

         With a TAGLINE tooltype of TAGLINE=%I"Signature"%V"SigTags"
         and the file "SigTags" containing:

                  134_TREK [134_TREK Moderator]%n...%R@"PlainTrekTags"
                  TREK %n...%R@"PersonalTrekTags""PlainTrekTags"
                  DefaultSig %n%R"GeneralTags"
                  uu_amiga_games
                  Members %n%S"AMUCTags"

         You will get the appropriate tag outputted, depending on the
         SIG IceOLR is currently in. In this example, the SIG
         uu_amiga_games will not have any output. The TREK sig uses 2
         possible tagfiles. "PersonalTrekTags" will always be used when
         Author: information is available, otherwise "PlainTrekTags" will
         be used.

@endnode

@node Doc.CountingIndex "IceIQle, Doc: CountingIndex"
AUTOMATIC PHRASE-FILE COUNTING and INDEX GENERATION
---------------------------------------------------

   Use this for quickly updating the number of headers or tags you have
   in any phrase files you're using. You can count manually if you prefer,
   but if your file is large this is easier. Before using this for the first
   time, make sure the first line of the phrase file to be updated has at
   least 6 characters of number digits or spaces...anything that can be
   overwritten to hold the updated value.

FROM WORKBENCH:

      Extend-Selectą all the phrase files to be updated. While continuing
      to hold down the shift key, double click the IceIQle icon.
      Alternatively, you could set the default tool of your phrase file
      to IceIQle, then just double click the phrase file.

         ą  Extend-Select means to FIRST click the first icon of all
            selections, THEN press and hold shift, then click on all the
            remaining files to be selected.

|>    Count/Update Requester:

      For each file selected you will be given the opportunity to
      specify a delimiter character (defaults to '@'), and whether or
      not to create an index file associated with the phrase file for
      quicker extraction. If you choose to create an index, its name
      will be the same as the phrasefile with a suffix of ".index".
      It will only be generated if there are more than 100 phrases
      because otherwise the overhead involved in opening and scanning
      the index counteracts any speed gain. If there IS an existing
      index file and you DON'T select "Create Index", the out of date
      index will be deleted. This is because when including random or
      sequential phrases, the index file is looked for and is used
      automatically if it exists.
      Then, simply select 'Count & Update' to count and write the correct
      total to the first line, or else press 'Cancel' to abort the
      operation.

      There is a method of avoiding the need to answer the requester
      every time. On the first line of your phrase file, leave a few
      spaces after the count number, then insert the text delimiter=@
      (or whatever your delimiter is). delimiter=n indicates no
      delimiter (single line phrases or tags). With this information
      in the phrase file, you won't be prompted at all when counting.
      The file is just updated and an index file WILL be generated.

FROM CLI:

      Only one file at a time can be updated. Just type:

            iceiqle -c[i] [@] filename

      The spaces are required. The [] characters are not typed, but
      indicate optional text. The optional @ is the phrase delimiter.
      If omitted, the phrase file is assumed to contain single line
      phrases, and the number of lines is simply counted. The 'i'
      parameter indicates an index file with suffix ".index" should
      be generated for faster phrase extraction. It will only be
      generated if there are more than 100 phrases because otherwise the
      overhead involved in opening and scanning the index counteracts any
      speed gain. If there IS an existing index file and you DON'T
      specify the 'i' parameter, the out of date index will be deleted.
      This is because when including random or sequential phrases, the
      index file is looked for and is used automatically if it exists.

@endnode

@node Doc.History "IceIQle, Doc: History"
HISTORY
-------

   v2.0  -  Made the initialed quoting mechanism work with the AmiQWK
            Off-Line message reader.
            Just make sure you set the Quote Prefix to empty and have
            the 'Header info in replies' checkbox checked in the
            Config/Replies Requester. Also, to use IceIQle's wordwrapping,
            set AmiQWK's Wrap/Trunc gadget to Wrap, and set the value to 99.
            This way, IceIQle's wordwrapping feature will work properly.

   v1.85 -  Made the Count/Index requester open on the currently active
            screen if it's public, otherwise WorkBench.

   v1.84 -  Corrected problem with %R or %S duplicating part of the
            last line of a phrase on occasion.

         -  Made the Count/Index requester always open on either OLR's or
            TERM's screen if that screen is the currently active one,
            otherwise on the WorkBench screen.
            Also, the requester now properly handles variable font heights
            in the title bar, as might happen when using the FONT=
            tooltype of OLR, or changing the default system font.

   v1.83 -  Made all FileInfoBlocks Word aligned. (was causing bizarre
            problems)

   v1.82 -  Uses the Topaz font everywhere in the Counting/Index
            generation requester so it's always readable.

   v1.81 -  Creates an empty message file if the requested file to tag
            or quote doesn't exist. For example, when posting in AmiQWK.

   v1.8  -  Compares the date stamps of tag or header files with their
            indexes when used and prompts you to regenerate the index on
            the fly whenever it is out of date. The tag/header file is
            also recounted and updated, so as long as you're using an
            index you don't really have to worry about maintaining the
            correct count after editing tagfiles...it will be done for
            you the next time that particular tag file is invoked.

         -  Included AmigaGuide format documentation.

         -  Fixed bug with %R selecting the very first line (count line)
            with single line phrase files (no delimiters) when used in
            conjunction with index files.

   v1.7  -  Added a SIG dependent control mechanism to allow different
            definitions of headers, taglines, and signatures depending
            on what SIG you are currently reading. See the %V control.

         -  Allowed 2 possible files to include with any %R, %S, %I,
            %C or %V control. The second file will be used if there is
            no Author: information available to IceIQle. This allows you
            to split tagfiles into 2 files: those that have embedded
            author information and those that don't. This way, usage of
            tags with embedded author information can be avoided when
            POSTING new messages.

   v1.62 -  Fixed Mungwall Hits.

   v1.61 -  Added a QUOTING=OFF tooltype to disable the quoting mechanism
            entirely. This allows use of IceIQle strictly as a tagline
            generator with any message reader that calls an external editor.

   v1.6  -  Added phrase-file indexing to make tag line inclusion
            significantly faster when using large tag files. Usage is
            described in the 'Automatic Phrase File Counting' section.

   v1.51 -  Fixed occasional undesired invocation of word-wrap when the
            WORDWRAP tooltype WASN'T present - due to uninitialized variable.

         -  Uses " > " as the quote string when replying to messages
            with the author field missing, as sometimes occurs on UseNet.

   v1.5  -  Uses less stack space so it won't overflow when using nested
            phrase files.

         -  Made TAGMAIL work when posting new EMail.

         -  Made the OMIT tooltype case insensitive.

         -  Maintains paragraph indent level while word-wrapping, so that if
            each line of the original paragraph is indented by, say, ten
            spaces, it will all remain indented by ten spaces even after
            being word-wrapped.

            Also now removes leading spaces from words at the beginning of a
            word wrapped line that could appear from the previous line if
            it had multiple spaces separating words or sentences.

            Also, detecting end of paragraph while word-wrapping should work
            99.999% of the time now because of the following addition:
               If the line following the currently wrapped line has an
               indent level greater than the wrapped line, this signifies
               the current line should be an end of paragraph.
            You still need the WRAPMARGIN value to handle paragraphs that
            aren't indented and aren't separated by at least 2 carriage
            returns (extremely rare).

   v1.41 -  Corrected misquoting of lines that begin with non-alphabetic
            characters followed immediately by '>'. For example, lines
            that start with:  1>    or  :>

   v1.4  -  Added horizontal tabbing for headers, phrase files, etc.
            with the %T control.

         -  Allowed optional omission of processing by IceIQle of certain
            types of files sent by IceTERM. For example, when creating the
            long description of uploaded files, having headers and taglines
            isn't really appropriate. See the OMIT tooltype.

         -  Added word wrap for quoted text with the WORDWRAP tooltype.

         -  Added EMail specific taglines using the TAGMAIL tooltype.

         -  Added automatic phrase file counting from WorkBench or CLI.
            (Not trying to out-do you Ken! Just thought it should be here.)

            Note: Handling of delimiters in phrase files has been changed
                  slightly. They MUST appear in the first column of any
                  line they're used in. This is to allow the possibility
                  of using the delimiter character in the actual text of
                  your tagfiles...I have discovered some with '@' in them.
                  So, if for some strange reason your delimiters weren't in
                  the first column, you'll have to change them.

   v1.3  -  Changed name to IceIQle. You should change any references
            to IQ to IceIQle instead (tooltypes most importantly).

         -  Added bragline with version number.

         -  Allowed use of %R and %S controls in any signature, header or
            tagline file. This gives the ability to include files from
            within files from within files....Recursion is limited to
            10 levels deep to prevent an endless loop.

   v1.21 -  REALLY fixed bug with Random Phrase selection never using
            the last phrase and including a blank phrase instead of the
            first one.

   v1.2a -  ATTEMPTED to fix bug with Random Phrase selection never using
            the last phrase and including a blank phrase instead of the
            first one.

   v1.2  -  Random and sequential header, tagline and signature
            inclusion from text files.
            See the HEADER and TAGLINE tooltypes for a description.

   v1.1  -  Added customizable header strings with embedded author
            name, address name, subject, date, etc.

         -  Made the EDITOR= tooltype in IceIQle unnecessary by allowing
            EDITOR=  tooltypes in IceOLR and IceTERM of the form:

               EDITOR=IceIQle Editor EditorArgs

            If only Editor=IceIQle is specified in IceOLR or IceTERM, then
            an EDITOR= tooltype in IceIQle is looked for.

         -  Removed any blank lines that are created when posting new
            messages. This includes the spaces and newline characters
            OLR and TERM generate, as well as any generated by the
            APPENDLINES option.

   v1.0  -  Initial Release

@endnode

